positive density. If\n    40→$A$ is its intersection with $(N/2, N)$ then $|A| \\gg N$ for all large $N$, yet no three\n    41→elements $a_1, a_2, a_3 \\in A$ and distinct primes $p_1, p_2, p_3$ satisfy\n    42→$a_1 p_1 = a_2 p_2 = a_3 p_3$.\n    43→-/\n    44→@[category research solved, AMS 5 11]\n    45→theorem erdos_537 : answer(False) ↔\n    46→    ∀ (ε : ℝ), 0 < ε →\n    47→    ∃ N₀ : ℕ, ∀ N : ℕ, N₀ ≤ N →\n    48→      ∀ A : Finset ℕ, A ⊆ Icc 1 N → ε * ↑N ≤ ↑A.card →\n    49→        ∃ a₁ ∈ A, ∃ a₂ ∈ A, ∃ a₃ ∈ A,\n    50→          ∃ p₁ p₂ p₃ : ℕ,\n    51→            Nat.Prime p₁ ∧ Nat.Prime p₂ ∧ Nat.Prime p₃ ∧\n    52→            p₁ ≠ p₂ ∧ p₁ ≠ p₃ ∧ p₂ ≠ p₃ ∧\n    53→            a₁ * p₁ = a₂ * p₂ ∧ a₁ * p₁ = a₃ * p₃ := by\n    54→  sorry\n    55→\n    56→end Erdos537\n    57→"}]},"uuid":"1cb664ca-846e-4b80-9ca8-1746dad638e0","timestamp":"2026-03-10T13:40:17.935Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4186d089-5dcb-4239-9e25-9590a28b5c8d"}
